post_text:
Achieve Language Academy will be closed Monday, March 16 and Tuesday, March 17, because we are beginning to implement mitigation strategies to help slow the spread of the Coronavirus Disease (COVID-19). This in addition to the announcement Governor Tim Walz made this morning that all schools will close March 18-27.

Staff should report to school on Monday to work on our distance learning plan.

More detailed information will be available soon, please check your email and visit https://www.achievemn.org/coronavirus-update.

It's time for you to get to know another one of our amazing staff a little bit better. Give Ms. Wenker an #AchieveStars shout out in the comments below!

"My name is Andrea Wenker. I am the ELL/Academic Support teacher for grades 5-8. This is my eleventh school year at Achieve. During my time at Achieve I have worked in a variety of roles and with many grade levels.

One of my great joys currently is working with my now middle school students who are my former PreK students! I am passionate about the work that I do with students and families, and I am fortunate to get to do the work I love with a great team of co-workers.

When I am not at school I enjoy reading, writing, baking, and cooking. I like to stay involved with my neighborhood community and attend community events. Most importantly, I LOVE spending time with my immediate and large extended family!

Happy Friday to you all, #AchieveStars family!

Today we're excited for you to get to know our very own Mrs. Hanson a little bit better. Feel free to give her a shout out in the comments below.

"This is my seventh year as a Tier II reading teacher at Achieve. I teach reading, writing, and comprehension skills to students in first through fourth grade.

I love working at Achieve because of the students and staff! Both are hardworking, kind, and welcoming, which has created the special community we have at Achieve Language Academy.

My husband and I have a daughter, son, and a little dog named Colby! These three keep us busy playing, exploring, and learning every day."

post_text:
Good morning, #AchieveStars family! This morning you can get to know our very own Ms. Strand a little better. Give her a shout out in the comments below!

"Hi! I'm Roz Strand and I am the Early Childhood Special Education Teacher at Achieve Language Academy. This is my first year at Achieve, but my 13th year in ECSE!

I live with my husband, Anthony, and my two children in Roseville. In the summer, we like to go on family bike rides, take road trips, and visit parks in Minnesota. In the winter, we play outside, bake, and enjoy playing games together. I sing in a choir, knit/crochet, and read A LOT!

At Achieve, I get to play many fun games with students. We explore tools that help us learn. My favorite part of my job is learning about my students and their families. Everyone has such interesting talents, traditions, and stories! Achieve is filled with amazing kiddos and I'm excited to work here!"
